{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"ample-famous-cockatiel","description":"## Why\nrebar depends on the GitHub OIDC provider that snap's dead terraform owns, and the domain-wide wildcard cert + auth_host SSO stack are to be kept alive under rebar (user decision). All must move from snap's `snap-demo-tfstate` shared state into rebar's `rebar-tfstate` state, owned by rebar's `infra/terraform`.\n\n## What\nAdd the 18 adopted resources to rebar's terraform, import the live objects into rebar state, apply the retag, and release them from snap's state.\n\n- New `infra/terraform/oidc.tf` (or add to `iam.tf`): `aws_iam_openid_connect_provider.github` (url `https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com`, client_id `sts.amazonaws.com`, thumbprint `6938fd4d98bab03faadb97b34396831e3780aea1`), tagged `Project = rebar`; rewire `iam.tf`'s `gha_terraform_plan_assume` to reference `.arn`.\n- New `infra/terraform/acm.tf`: wildcard cert `*.solutions.navateam.com` + DNS validation records + validation (uses rebar's existing `dns_zone_id` var).\n- New `infra/terraform/auth_sso.tf`: cookie-signing SSM SecureString + `random_password` + Google-client-secret data source + SSO locals.\n- New `infra/terraform/auth_host.tf`: Lambda + IAM role/policy + API GW v2 (api/integration/route/stage) + lambda permission + CloudFront distribution + Route53 A/AAAA + origin secret.\n- Copy Lambda source `infra/terraform/auth/auth-host/index.js` + `auth/lib/cookie.js` (needed by `archive_file`).\n- Preserve physical names via a `legacy_name_prefix = \"snap-demo\"` local (renaming = recreate).\n- `terraform import` each live resource; import the two `random_password` resources with their LIVE values (read from SSM / the Lambda env) so no secret rotates.\n- `terraform state rm` the adopted resources from snap's `infra/shared` state.\n\n## Scope\nTerraform + Lambda source + the live import/apply/state-rm only. Docs are a separate child. Does NOT adopt snap's `github_deploy` role, audit-dashboard sso-gate, ECS/ECR/VPC/RDS (snap-app resources).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `aws_iam_openid_connect_provider.github` is in `infra/terraform`, tagged `Project=rebar`, and the drift role references its `.arn`.\n- [ ] Wildcard cert + auth_sso + auth_host resources are in `infra/terraform` with physical names preserved and `Project=rebar` tags where the resource type supports tags.\n- [ ] `make lint` / `terraform fmt -check` / `terraform validate` pass on the new files.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] All 18 resources imported into rebar state; `terraform plan` shows no destroy/replace and no secret-value change (evidence: plan output as a comment).\n- [ ] [operator-attested] `terraform apply` completed (retag applied); resources removed from snap's shared state (evidence recorded as a comment).","id":"7246-bd9e-58a3-41fd","parent_id":"d58f-7581-1f72-4372","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Adopt snap shared resources into rebar terraform + live import/apply/retag"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784043686213922001,"uuid":"d0ad2b6c-a039-492b-906e-4cf1aef73097"}